WEBVTT

00:11.344 --> 00:13.388
<i>So let's look at the statistics.</i>

00:13.471 --> 00:17.560
<i>The United States is home
to 5% of the world's population...</i>

00:19.352 --> 00:22.022
<i>but 25% of the world's prisoners.</i>

00:24.567 --> 00:26.193
<i>Think about that.</i>

00:28.529 --> 00:31.198
<i>A little country with 5%
of the world's population</i>

00:31.281 --> 00:34.785
<i>having 25% of the world's prisoners?</i>

00:34.868 --> 00:35.953
One out of four?

00:36.036 --> 00:40.040
One out of four human beings
with their hands on bars, shackled,

00:40.123 --> 00:43.919
in the world are locked up here,
in the land of the free.

00:46.338 --> 00:49.299
We had a prison population of 300,000
in 1972.

00:49.382 --> 00:53.178
Today, we have a prison population
of 2.3 million.

00:53.261 --> 00:56.724
The United States now has the highest rate
of incarceration in the world.

00:59.226 --> 01:02.145
So, you see, now suddenly
they're in an awakening that,

01:02.229 --> 01:05.608
"Oh, perhaps we need to downsize
our prison system.

01:05.691 --> 01:09.486
It's gotten too expensive.
It's gotten out of hand."

01:09.570 --> 01:15.158
Um, but the very folks
who often express so much concern,

01:15.242 --> 01:19.329
uh, about the cost
and the expanse of the system

01:19.412 --> 01:23.250
are often very unwilling
to talk in any serious way

01:23.333 --> 01:25.878
about remedying the harm
that has been done.

01:28.546 --> 01:32.009
History is not just
stuff that happens by accident.

01:32.092 --> 01:36.596
We are the products of the history
that our ancestors chose, if we're white.

01:36.680 --> 01:39.516
If we are black, we are products
of the history that our ancestors

01:39.600 --> 01:41.310
most likely did not choose.

01:41.393 --> 01:45.063
Yet here we all are together,
the products of that set of choices.

01:45.147 --> 01:48.776
And we have to understand that
in order to escape from it.

01:54.031 --> 01:56.366
<i>The 13th Amendment to the Constitution</i>

01:56.449 --> 02:00.871
<i>makes it unconstitutional
for someone to be held as a slave.</i>

02:00.954 --> 02:03.248
<i>In other words, it grants freedom...</i>

02:06.168 --> 02:08.628
<i>to all Americans.</i>

02:09.545 --> 02:13.967
<i>There are exceptions, including criminals.</i>

02:15.510 --> 02:19.097
<i>There's a clause, a loophole.</i>

02:19.681 --> 02:21.892
<i>If you have that
in the structure,</i>

02:21.975 --> 02:24.561
<i>in this constitutional language,</i>

02:24.645 --> 02:26.897
<i>then it's there to be used as a tool</i>

02:26.980 --> 02:29.608
<i>for whichever purposes
one wants to use it.</i>

