49:22.209 --> 49:26.672
<i>And what did they find? They found limbs
and heads just strewn all over the place.</i>

49:27.172 --> 49:29.884
<i>I remember,
from the time I was very small,</i>

49:29.967 --> 49:33.763
<i>I remember the sounds of bombs
exploding across the street.</i>

49:33.846 --> 49:35.305
Our house shaking.

49:35.389 --> 49:39.894
I remember my father having to have guns
at his disposal at all times

49:39.977 --> 49:46.108
because of the fact that at any moment
we might expect to be attacked.

49:46.191 --> 49:50.404
I mean, that's why,
when someone asks me about violence, uh...

49:51.446 --> 49:53.991
I just, uh...
I just find it incredible.

49:54.074 --> 49:57.411
Because what it means is that
the person who's asking that question

49:57.494 --> 50:01.165
has absolutely no idea
what black people have gone through,

50:01.248 --> 50:03.543
what black people have experienced
in this country

50:03.626 --> 50:08.130
since the time the first black person
was kidnapped from the shores of Africa.

50:09.048 --> 50:11.717
<i>And when you strip out
a whole generation of leadership,</i>

50:11.801 --> 50:14.804
running folk out the country,
killing folk, framing folk,

50:14.887 --> 50:18.098
you will be vulnerable
to Bill Clinton or anybody else.

50:18.182 --> 50:20.142
They'll do to you what they will.

